CBRE as the exclusive agents are pleased to present 79 Glebe Point Road, Glebe.

Conveniently positioned along Glebe’s main dining and retail strip, 79 Glebe Point Road presents a secure retail investment opportunity in one of Sydney’s most up-and-coming suburbs. The property is tenanted by Otto Noorba Restaurant and has
288sqm* of NLA, a large outdoor seating area plus 6 secure car spaces. 

A development scheme has been prepared to capitalise on the large site area by constructing residential apartments in the back courtyard space (STCA).

79 Glebe Poing Road benefits from the following key attributes:
• Ground floor restaurant with a total NLA of 288sqm*, large outdoor dining area plus 6 car spaces
• Anchored by well-known tenant with a strong catchment of customers
• Secure lease with 5+5 year options
• Net passing income: $170,307 per annum*
• Premium location along Glebe Point Road, moments from Broadway and several prestigious universities
• Significant landholding boasting rear street access
• Direct light rail and bus services to Sydney CBD (5-minute ride*)
• Large young professional and student demographic
• Design scheme prepared for further extensions to the property (STCA)

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the selling agents.

CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present 33 Glebe Point Road, Glebe. Comprising a newly refurbished restaurant on the ground floor and a three bedroom apartment above, the property presents a secure investment in one of Sydney's fast growing suburbs. The property boasts a high profile location along Glebe Point Road, just moments from Broadway Shopping Centre, Sydney University and Glebe Markets.

33 Glebe Point Road benefits from the following key attributes:

- Ground floor restaurant plus three-bedroom unit with total NLA of 268sqm*
- Leased to cafe-style restaurant 'Dispensary 1908' until June 2021 with 3 year option
- Gross passing income: $124,671 per annum*
- High profile location on arterial road – strong foot &  vehicular traffic
- Two minute walk* to Broadway Shopping Centre, Glebe Markets & Sydney University
- Direct buses to Sydney CBD (5 minute ride*)
- Large catchment of young professionals and students

The property will be sold via public auction on Tuesday, 3 March 2020 at 10.30am. 

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate

Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.
